message.content:
A ray is a type of aquatic fish that belongs to the shark family.
They have a distinctive flattened body shape with a long, pointed snout.
Rays typically have smooth, leathery skin and can range in color from dark brown to gray to spotted.
They are found in both saltwater and freshwater environments around the world.
Rays are known for their unique way of swimming, undulating their bodies up and down to glide through the water.
Some species of ray have venomous spines on their tails for self-defense.
In captivity, rays are popular attractions in aquariums due to their unique appearance and behaviors.
